I had the same issue with Infura on the Ropsten network. I wasn't providing a gasPrice when I got the "transaction underpriced" error; only gas. Looks like I had to provide all transaction parameters except nonce like below if not managed by geth and if signing the transaction myself. Transaction went through fine right after.

{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"error":{"code":-32000,"message":"transaction underpriced"}}

`web3.eth.sendTransaction({
    from: from,
    to: to,
    value: value,
    gasPrice: "20000000000",
    gas: "21000"
}, function(error, result){
    if(error)
    {	
    }
    else
    {
    }
})`

{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":3,"result":"0xe47688ed9bc2b9d4f631b0a94b7a40dd83ab884ec1493e3ba9b741da67b3a83b"}

Still happening on Ropsten using Infura. web3 version`0.20.6` and geth `1.8.8-stable`.

```
const genRawTx = async () => {
	const count = await web3.eth.getTransactionCount(ADDRESS);
	const nonce = web3.toHex(count);

	const gasPrice = web3.eth.gasPrice.toNumber() * 1.50;
	console.log('web3.eth.gasPrice.toNumber()',  web3.eth.gasPrice.toNumber());

	return {
		'from': from,
		'nonce': nonce,
		'gasPrice': '0x09184e72a000', // 0x09184e72a000 is 10 quadrillions wei
		'gasLimit': '0x2710', // 0x2710 is 10,000
		'to': to,
		'value': '0x10',
		'data': contract.transfer.getData(to, 10, { from: from }),
		'chainId': '0x03'
	};
};
```
